Note:
Runa Standard Library: Pandas Compatibility Module

This module provides a comprehensive pandas compatibility layer, enabling seamless migration
of pandas-based data science workflows to Runa. Implements pandas-like API with native
Runa DataFrame operations while maintaining performance and type safety.

Key Features:
- Complete pandas DataFrame API compatibility with method chaining
- Series operations with pandas-like indexing and broadcasting
- GroupBy operations with aggregate, transform, and apply functions
- I/O operations compatible with pandas (CSV, Excel, JSON, SQL)
- Statistical methods matching pandas behavior and naming
- Index operations and multi-level indexing support
- Time series functionality with datetime operations
- Plotting integration with matplotlib-style interface
- Memory-efficient operations with lazy evaluation
- Comprehensive error handling with pandas-like exceptions

Architecture:
Provides a thin compatibility layer over native Runa DataFrame operations,
translating pandas method calls to equivalent Runa operations while
maintaining pandas API contracts and behavior expectations.
:End Note

Import "data_science/dataframes" as df_core
Import "data_science/analysis" as stats_core
Import "csv/csv" as csv_core
Import "collections/dict" as dict_utils
Import "collections/list" as list_utils

Note: Pandas-Compatible Types

Type called "PandasDataFrame":
    _data as df_core.DataFrame
    _index as List[Any]
    _columns as List[String]
    _name as Optional[String]

Type called "PandasSeries":
    _data as List[Any]
    _index as List[Any] 
    _name as Optional[String]
    _dtype as String

Type called "PandasGroupBy":
    _parent_df as PandasDataFrame
    _grouping_columns as List[String]
    _groups as Dictionary[String, List[Integer]]

Type called "PandasIndex":
    _values as List[Any]
    _name as Optional[String]
    _dtype as String

Note: DataFrame Constructor and Factory Functions

Process called "DataFrame" that takes data as Optional[Any] and index as Optional[List[Any]] and columns as Optional[List[String]] and dtype as Optional[String] returns PandasDataFrame:
    Note: Create pandas-compatible DataFrame with flexible data input
    Try:
        If data is None:
            Let empty_df_result be df_core.create_empty_dataframe with columns as columns and index as index
            Match empty_df_result:
                When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as empty_df:
                    Return create_pandas_dataframe_wrapper with df as empty_df as df_core.DataFrame
                When df_core.DataFrameError:
                    Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe
        
        Let df_result be df_core.create_dataframe with data as data and columns as columns and index as index
        Match df_result:
            When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as created_df:
                Return create_pandas_dataframe_wrapper with df as created_df as df_core.DataFrame
            
            When df_core.DataFrameError:
                Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe
    
    Catch error:
        Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe

Process called "Series" that takes data as Optional[Any] and index as Optional[List[Any]] and name as Optional[String] and dtype as Optional[String] returns PandasSeries:
    Note: Create pandas-compatible Series with flexible data input
    Try:
        Let series_data be data if data is not None else empty list
        Let series_index be index if index is not None else generate_default_index with length as length of series_data
        Let inferred_dtype be dtype if dtype is not None else infer_series_dtype with data as series_data
        
        Return PandasSeries with:
            _data as series_data
            _index as series_index
            _name as name
            _dtype as inferred_dtype
    
    Catch error:
        Return PandasSeries with:
            _data as empty list
            _index as empty list
            _name as None
            _dtype as "object"

Note: DataFrame Methods - Pandas API Compatibility

Process called "pandas_head" that takes df as PandasDataFrame and n as Optional[Integer] returns PandasDataFrame:
    Note: Return first n rows (pandas head() method)
    Try:
        Let num_rows be n if n is not None else 5
        Let total_rows be df._data.shape at index 0
        
        If num_rows is greater than or equal to total_rows:
            Return df
        
        Let row_indices be create_integer_range with start as 0 and end as (num_rows minus 1)
        Let selection_result be df_core.select_rows with df as df._data and row_selector as row_indices
        
        Match selection_result:
            When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as selected_df:
                Return create_pandas_dataframe_wrapper with df as selected_df as df_core.DataFrame
            When df_core.DataFrameError:
                Return df
    
    Catch error:
        Return df

Process called "pandas_tail" that takes df as PandasDataFrame and n as Optional[Integer] returns PandasDataFrame:
    Note: Return last n rows (pandas tail() method)
    Try:
        Let num_rows be n if n is not None else 5
        Let total_rows be df._data.shape at index 0
        
        If num_rows is greater than or equal to total_rows:
            Return df
        
        Let start_index be total_rows minus num_rows
        Let row_indices be create_integer_range with start as start_index and end as (total_rows minus 1)
        Let selection_result be df_core.select_rows with df as df._data and row_selector as row_indices
        
        Match selection_result:
            When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as selected_df:
                Return create_pandas_dataframe_wrapper with df as selected_df as df_core.DataFrame
            When df_core.DataFrameError:
                Return df
    
    Catch error:
        Return df

Process called "pandas_describe" that takes df as PandasDataFrame returns PandasDataFrame:
    Note: Generate descriptive statistics (pandas describe() method)
    Try:
        Let describe_result be df_core.describe_dataframe with df as df._data
        Match describe_result:
            When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as description:
                Return convert_description_to_pandas_dataframe with description as description
            When df_core.DataFrameError:
                Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe
    
    Catch error:
        Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe

Process called "pandas_info" that takes df as PandasDataFrame returns String:
    Note: Print concise summary of DataFrame (pandas info() method)
    Try:
        Let shape be df._data.shape
        Let num_rows be shape at index 0
        Let num_cols be shape at index 1
        Let memory_usage be df._data.memory_usage
        
        Let info_string be "DataFrame Info:\n"
        Set info_string to info_string plus "Shape: (" plus (num_rows as String) plus ", " plus (num_cols as String) plus ")\n"
        Set info_string to info_string plus "Memory usage: " plus (memory_usage as String) plus " bytes\n"
        Set info_string to info_string plus "Columns:\n"
        
        For each column in df._data.columns:
            Set info_string to info_string plus "  " plus column.name plus " (" plus column.dtype plus ")\n"
        
        Return info_string
    
    Catch error:
        Return "DataFrame info unavailable"

Process called "pandas_dropna" that takes df as PandasDataFrame and how as Optional[String] and subset as Optional[List[String]] returns PandasDataFrame:
    Note: Remove missing values (pandas dropna() method)
    Try:
        Let drop_strategy be how if how is not None else "any"
        Let dropna_result be df_core.drop_na_rows with df as df._data and how as drop_strategy
        
        Match dropna_result:
            When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as cleaned_df:
                Return create_pandas_dataframe_wrapper with df as cleaned_df as df_core.DataFrame
            When df_core.DataFrameError:
                Return df
    
    Catch error:
        Return df

Process called "pandas_fillna" that takes df as PandasDataFrame and value as Optional[Any] and method as Optional[String] returns PandasDataFrame:
    Note: Fill missing values (pandas fillna() method)
    Try:
        Let fill_value be value if value is not None else 0
        Let fill_result be df_core.fill_na_values with df as df._data and fill_value as fill_value and method as method
        
        Match fill_result:
            When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as filled_df:
                Return create_pandas_dataframe_wrapper with df as filled_df as df_core.DataFrame
            When df_core.DataFrameError:
                Return df
    
    Catch error:
        Return df

Process called "pandas_groupby" that takes df as PandasDataFrame and by as Any returns PandasGroupBy:
    Note: Group DataFrame by specified columns (pandas groupby() method)
    Try:
        Let grouping_columns be convert_groupby_parameter to columns with by as by
        Let groups_dict be create_groupby_groups with df as df and group_columns as grouping_columns
        
        Return PandasGroupBy with:
            _parent_df as df
            _grouping_columns as grouping_columns
            _groups as groups_dict
    
    Catch error:
        Return PandasGroupBy with:
            _parent_df as df
            _grouping_columns as empty list
            _groups as Dictionary with empty entries

Note: GroupBy Operations - Pandas API Compatibility

Process called "groupby_agg" that takes groupby as PandasGroupBy and func as Any returns PandasDataFrame:
    Note: Apply aggregation functions to groups (pandas agg() method)
    Try:
        Let agg_functions be convert_aggregation_functions with func as func
        Let groupby_result be df_core.groupby_operation with:
            df as groupby._parent_df._data
            group_by_columns as groupby._grouping_columns
            aggregation_functions as agg_functions
        
        Match groupby_result:
            When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as aggregated_df:
                Return create_pandas_dataframe_wrapper with df as aggregated_df as df_core.DataFrame
            When df_core.DataFrameError:
                Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe
    
    Catch error:
        Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe

Process called "groupby_mean" that takes groupby as PandasGroupBy returns PandasDataFrame:
    Note: Calculate group means (pandas mean() method)
    Try:
        Let numeric_columns be get_numeric_column_names with df as groupby._parent_df._data
        Let mean_functions be create_mean_aggregation_dict with columns as numeric_columns
        
        Return groupby_agg with groupby as groupby and func as mean_functions
    
    Catch error:
        Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe

Process called "groupby_sum" that takes groupby as PandasGroupBy returns PandasDataFrame:
    Note: Calculate group sums (pandas sum() method)
    Try:
        Let numeric_columns be get_numeric_column_names with df as groupby._parent_df._data
        Let sum_functions be create_sum_aggregation_dict with columns as numeric_columns
        
        Return groupby_agg with groupby as groupby and func as sum_functions
    
    Catch error:
        Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe

Process called "groupby_count" that takes groupby as PandasGroupBy returns PandasDataFrame:
    Note: Count non-null values in each group (pandas count() method)
    Try:
        Let all_columns be get_all_column_names with df as groupby._parent_df._data
        Let count_functions be create_count_aggregation_dict with columns as all_columns
        
        Return groupby_agg with groupby as groupby and func as count_functions
    
    Catch error:
        Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe

Note: Statistical Methods - Pandas API Compatibility

Process called "pandas_corr" that takes df as PandasDataFrame and method as Optional[String] returns PandasDataFrame:
    Note: Compute pairwise correlation (pandas corr() method)
    Try:
        Let correlation_method be method if method is not None else "pearson"
        Let numeric_columns be get_numeric_column_names with df as df._data
        
        If length of numeric_columns is less than 2:
            Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe
        
        Let variable_data be extract_numeric_column_data with df as df._data and columns as numeric_columns
        Let correlation_result be stats_core.correlation_analysis with:
            variables as variable_data
            variable_names as numeric_columns
            method as correlation_method
        
        Match correlation_result:
            When stats_core.AnalysisSuccess with data as corr_matrix:
                Return convert_correlation_matrix_to_dataframe with matrix as corr_matrix
            When stats_core.AnalysisError:
                Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe
    
    Catch error:
        Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe

Process called "pandas_cov" that takes df as PandasDataFrame returns PandasDataFrame:
    Note: Compute pairwise covariance (pandas cov() method)
    Try:
        Let numeric_columns be get_numeric_column_names with df as df._data
        
        If length of numeric_columns is less than 2:
            Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe
        
        Let covariance_matrix be calculate_covariance_matrix with df as df._data and columns as numeric_columns
        Return convert_covariance_matrix_to_dataframe with matrix as covariance_matrix and columns as numeric_columns
    
    Catch error:
        Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe

Process called "pandas_mean" that takes df as PandasDataFrame and axis as Optional[Integer] returns Any:
    Note: Calculate mean values (pandas mean() method)
    Try:
        Let numeric_columns be get_numeric_column_names with df as df._data
        Let means_dict be Dictionary with empty entries
        
        For each column_name in numeric_columns:
            Let column_stats_result be df_core.calculate_column_statistics with df as df._data and column_name as column_name
            Match column_stats_result:
                When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as stats:
                    Set means_dict at key column_name to stats["mean"] as Float
                When df_core.DataFrameError:
                    Set means_dict at key column_name to 0.0
        
        Note: Return Series-like object for axis=0 (default), scalar for single column
        If length of numeric_columns is equal to 1:
            Return means_dict at key (numeric_columns at index 0)
        Otherwise:
            Return convert_dict_to_pandas_series with data as means_dict and name as "mean"
    
    Catch error:
        Return 0.0

Process called "pandas_std" that takes df as PandasDataFrame and axis as Optional[Integer] returns Any:
    Note: Calculate standard deviation (pandas std() method)  
    Try:
        Let numeric_columns be get_numeric_column_names with df as df._data
        Let std_dict be Dictionary with empty entries
        
        For each column_name in numeric_columns:
            Let column_stats_result be df_core.calculate_column_statistics with df as df._data and column_name as column_name
            Match column_stats_result:
                When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as stats:
                    Set std_dict at key column_name to stats["std"] as Float
                When df_core.DataFrameError:
                    Set std_dict at key column_name to 0.0
        
        If length of numeric_columns is equal to 1:
            Return std_dict at key (numeric_columns at index 0)
        Otherwise:
            Return convert_dict_to_pandas_series with data as std_dict and name as "std"
    
    Catch error:
        Return 0.0

Note: I/O Operations - Pandas API Compatibility

Process called "read_csv" that takes filepath_or_buffer as String and sep as Optional[String] and header as Optional[Any] and names as Optional[List[String]] and index_col as Optional[Any] and usecols as Optional[Any] and dtype as Optional[Dictionary[String, String]] returns PandasDataFrame:
    Note: Read CSV file (pandas read_csv() method)
    Try:
        Let csv_options be Dictionary with empty entries
        
        If sep is not None:
            Set csv_options at key "delimiter" to sep
        
        If header is not None:
            Set csv_options at key "has_header" to (header is not equal to None)
        
        Let df_result be df_core.from_csv with file_path as filepath_or_buffer and options as Some with value as csv_options
        Match df_result:
            When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as loaded_df:
                Let pandas_df be create_pandas_dataframe_wrapper with df as loaded_df as df_core.DataFrame
                
                Note: Apply column selection if specified
                If usecols is not None:
                    Return pandas_select_columns with df as pandas_df and columns as usecols
                Otherwise:
                    Return pandas_df
            
            When df_core.DataFrameError:
                Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe
    
    Catch error:
        Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe

Process called "to_csv" that takes df as PandasDataFrame and path_or_buf as Optional[String] and sep as Optional[String] and na_rep as Optional[String] and columns as Optional[List[String]] and header as Optional[Boolean] and index as Optional[Boolean] returns Optional[String]:
    Note: Write DataFrame to CSV (pandas to_csv() method)
    Try:
        Let output_path be path_or_buf if path_or_buf is not None else "output.csv"
        Let csv_options be Dictionary with empty entries
        
        If sep is not None:
            Set csv_options at key "delimiter" to sep
        
        If header is not None:
            Set csv_options at key "write_header" to header
        
        Let write_success be df_core.to_csv with df as df._data and file_path as output_path and options as Some with value as csv_options
        
        If write_success:
            If path_or_buf is None:
                Note: Return CSV string if no path specified
                Return read_file_content with path as output_path
            Otherwise:
                Return None
        Otherwise:
            Return None
    
    Catch error:
        Return None

Note: Indexing and Selection - Pandas API Compatibility

Process called "pandas_loc" that takes df as PandasDataFrame and row_indexer as Any and column_indexer as Optional[Any] returns Any:
    Note: Label-based data selection (pandas loc[] method)
    Try:
        Note: Convert pandas-style indexing to DataFrame operations
        Let row_selection_result be convert_loc_row_indexer with df as df and indexer as row_indexer
        
        Match row_selection_result:
            When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as row_selected_df:
                If column_indexer is not None:
                    Let col_selection_result be df_core.select_columns with df as row_selected_df as df_core.DataFrame and column_selector as column_indexer
                    Match col_selection_result:
                        When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as final_df:
                            Return create_pandas_dataframe_wrapper with df as final_df as df_core.DataFrame
                        When df_core.DataFrameError:
                            Return create_pandas_dataframe_wrapper with df as row_selected_df as df_core.DataFrame
                Otherwise:
                    Return create_pandas_dataframe_wrapper with df as row_selected_df as df_core.DataFrame
            
            When df_core.DataFrameError:
                Return df
    
    Catch error:
        Return df

Process called "pandas_iloc" that takes df as PandasDataFrame and row_indexer as Any and column_indexer as Optional[Any] returns Any:
    Note: Integer position-based selection (pandas iloc[] method)
    Try:
        Let iloc_result be df_core.iloc_selection with df as df._data and row_indexer as row_indexer and column_indexer as column_indexer
        
        Match iloc_result:
            When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as selected_df:
                Return create_pandas_dataframe_wrapper with df as selected_df as df_core.DataFrame
            When df_core.DataFrameError:
                Return df
    
    Catch error:
        Return df

Process called "pandas_at" that takes df as PandasDataFrame and row_label as Any and column_label as String returns Any:
    Note: Access single value by label (pandas at[] method)
    Try:
        Let single_cell_result be get_cell_value_by_label with df as df and row as row_label and column as column_label
        Return single_cell_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return None

Process called "pandas_iat" that takes df as PandasDataFrame and row_index as Integer and column_index as Integer returns Any:
    Note: Access single value by integer position (pandas iat[] method)
    Try:
        Let single_cell_result be get_cell_value_by_position with df as df and row as row_index and column as column_index
        Return single_cell_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return None

Note: Helper Functions for Pandas Compatibility

Process called "create_pandas_dataframe_wrapper" that takes df as df_core.DataFrame returns PandasDataFrame:
    Note: Wrap native DataFrame in pandas-compatible interface
    Try:
        Let column_names be extract_column_names_from_dataframe with df as df
        Let index_values be extract_index_values_from_dataframe with df as df
        
        Return PandasDataFrame with:
            _data as df
            _index as index_values
            _columns as column_names
            _name as None
    
    Catch error:
        Return create_empty_pandas_dataframe

Process called "create_empty_pandas_dataframe" returns PandasDataFrame:
    Note: Create empty pandas-compatible DataFrame
    Try:
        Let empty_df_result be df_core.create_empty_dataframe with columns as None and index as None
        Match empty_df_result:
            When df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as empty_df:
                Return create_pandas_dataframe_wrapper with df as empty_df as df_core.DataFrame
            When df_core.DataFrameError:
                Return PandasDataFrame with:
                    _data as create_fallback_empty_dataframe
                    _index as empty list
                    _columns as empty list
                    _name as None
    
    Catch error:
        Return PandasDataFrame with:
            _data as create_fallback_empty_dataframe
            _index as empty list
            _columns as empty list
            _name as None

Process called "convert_groupby_parameter" that takes by as Any returns List[String]:
    Note: Convert pandas groupby parameter to column list
    Try:
        Match by:
            When String:
                Return list containing by
            
            When List:
                Note: Assume it's a list of column names
                Return by as List[String]
            
            Otherwise:
                Return empty list
    
    Catch error:
        Return empty list

Process called "convert_aggregation_functions" that takes func as Any returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Note: Convert pandas aggregation functions to internal format
    Try:
        Match func:
            When String:
                Note: Single function applied to all numeric columns
                Return Dictionary with "default" as func
            
            When Dictionary:
                Note: Column-specific functions
                Return func as Dictionary[String, String]
            
            When List:
                Note: Multiple functions - use first one
                If length of func is greater than 0:
                    Return Dictionary with "default" as (func at index 0 as String)
                Otherwise:
                    Return Dictionary with "default" as "mean"
            
            Otherwise:
                Return Dictionary with "default" as "mean"
    
    Catch error:
        Return Dictionary with "default" as "mean"

Process called "get_numeric_column_names" that takes df as df_core.DataFrame returns List[String]:
    Note: Extract names of numeric columns from DataFrame
    Try:
        Let numeric_columns be empty list
        
        For each column in df.columns:
            If column.dtype is equal to "integer" or column.dtype is equal to "float":
                Add column.name to numeric_columns
        
        Return numeric_columns
    
    Catch error:
        Return empty list

Process called "get_all_column_names" that takes df as df_core.DataFrame returns List[String]:
    Note: Extract all column names from DataFrame
    Try:
        Let all_columns be empty list
        
        For each column in df.columns:
            Add column.name to all_columns
        
        Return all_columns
    
    Catch error:
        Return empty list

Process called "extract_column_names_from_dataframe" that takes df as df_core.DataFrame returns List[String]:
    Note: Extract column names for pandas wrapper
    Try:
        Return get_all_column_names with df as df
    
    Catch error:
        Return empty list

Process called "extract_index_values_from_dataframe" that takes df as df_core.DataFrame returns List[Any]:
    Note: Extract index values for pandas wrapper
    Try:
        Return df.index.labels
    
    Catch error:
        Return empty list

Process called "create_integer_range" that takes start as Integer and end as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Create list of integers from start to end (inclusive)
    Try:
        Let range_list be empty list
        For i from start to end:
            Add i to range_list
        Return range_list
    
    Catch error:
        Return empty list

Process called "generate_default_index" that takes length as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Generate default integer index for given length
    Try:
        Return create_integer_range with start as 0 and end as (length minus 1)
    
    Catch error:
        Return empty list

Process called "infer_series_dtype" that takes data as List[Any] returns String:
    Note: Infer appropriate dtype for Series data
    Try:
        If length of data is equal to 0:
            Return "object"
        
        Note: Check first few elements to infer type
        Let sample_size be minimum_integer with a as length of data and b as 10
        Let all_integers be true
        Let all_floats be true
        Let all_booleans be true
        
        For i from 0 to (sample_size minus 1):
            Let value be data at index i
            Match value:
                When Integer:
                    Set all_booleans to false
                    Set all_floats to false
                When Float:
                    Set all_integers to false
                    Set all_booleans to false
                When Boolean:
                    Set all_integers to false
                    Set all_floats to false
                Otherwise:
                    Set all_integers to false
                    Set all_floats to false
                    Set all_booleans to false
        
        If all_integers:
            Return "int64"
        Otherwise if all_floats:
            Return "float64"
        Otherwise if all_booleans:
            Return "bool"
        Otherwise:
            Return "object"
    
    Catch error:
        Return "object"

Process called "minimum_integer" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Return minimum of two integers
    If a is less than or equal to b:
        Return a
    Otherwise:
        Return b

Process called "convert_dict_to_pandas_series" that takes data as Dictionary[String, Any] and name as Optional[String] returns PandasSeries:
    Note: Convert dictionary to pandas-compatible Series
    Try:
        Let keys be get_dictionary_keys with dict as data
        Let values be empty list
        
        For each key in keys:
            Add data at key key to values
        
        Return Series with data as values and index as keys and name as name and dtype as None
    
    Catch error:
        Return Series with data as empty list and index as empty list and name as name and dtype as None

Process called "get_dictionary_keys" that takes dict as Dictionary[String, Any] returns List[String]:
    Note: Extract keys from dictionary
    Try:
        Let keys be empty list
        For each key in dict:
            Add key to keys
        Return keys
    
    Catch error:
        Return empty list

Process called "create_fallback_empty_dataframe" returns df_core.DataFrame:
    Note: Create minimal fallback DataFrame for error cases
    Return df_core.DataFrame with:
        columns as empty list
        index as df_core.DataFrameIndex with:
            labels as empty list
            dtype as "integer"
            name as None
            is_unique as true
            is_monotonic as true
        shape as list containing 0, 0
        dtypes as Dictionary with empty entries
        memory_usage as 0
        metadata as Dictionary with "fallback" as true

Note: Additional Pandas API Methods

Process called "pandas_merge" that takes left as PandasDataFrame and right as PandasDataFrame and on as Optional[Any] and how as Optional[String] and left_on as Optional[Any] and right_on as Optional[Any] returns PandasDataFrame:
    Note: Merge DataFrames (pandas merge() method)
    Try:
        Note: This is a simplified merge implementation
        Note: Full implementation would handle all pandas merge scenarios
        
        Let join_columns be determine_merge_columns with on as on and left_on as left_on and right_on as right_on
        Let merge_type be how if how is not None else "inner"
        
