        Return 0.0

Process called "series_std" that takes series as PandasSeries returns Float:
    Note: Calculate standard deviation of Series values
    Try:
        Let numeric_values be extract_numeric_values_from_series with series as series
        If length of numeric_values is less than 2:
            Return 0.0
        
        Let mean be series_mean with series as series
        Let sum_squared_deviations be 0.0
        
        For each value in numeric_values:
            Let deviation be value minus mean
            Set sum_squared_deviations to sum_squared_deviations plus (deviation times deviation)
        
        Let variance be sum_squared_deviations divided by ((length of numeric_values minus 1) as Float)
        Return calculate_square_root with number as variance
    
    Catch error:
        Return 0.0

