Process called "trim_whitespace" that takes text as String returns String:
    Note: Remove leading and trailing whitespace
    Try:
        Let start_index be 0
        Let end_index be length of text minus 1
        
        Note: Find first non-whitespace character
        For i from 0 to (length of text minus 1):
            Let char be character_at with text as text and index as i
            If char is not equal to " " and char is not equal to "\t" and char is not equal to "\n" and char is not equal to "\r":
                Set start_index to i
                Break
        
        Note: Find last non-whitespace character
        For i from (length of text minus 1) down to 0:
            Let char be character_at with text as text and index as i
            If char is not equal to " " and char is not equal to "\t" and char is not equal to "\n" and char is not equal to "\r":
                Set end_index to i
                Break
        
        If start_index is greater than end_index:
            Return ""
        
        Return substring with text as text and start as start_index and end as (end_index plus 1)
    
    Catch error:
        Return text

Process called "string_starts_with" that takes text as String and prefix as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if string starts with given prefix
    Try:
