Process called "remove_dataframe_duplicates" that takes df as df_core.DataFrame and columns as List[String] and keep_strategy as String returns df_core.DataFrameResult:
    Note: Remove duplicate rows from DataFrame
    Try:
        Note: For comprehensive duplicate removal, we need row comparison
        Note: This implementation removes exact duplicate rows
        Let unique_rows be empty list
        Let unique_data be Dictionary with empty entries
        
        Note: Initialize columns in unique_data
        For each col_name in df.columns:
            Set unique_data[col_name] to empty list
        
        Let row_count be 0
        If length of df.columns is greater than 0:
            Let first_col be df.columns at index 0
            If df.data contains key first_col:
                Set row_count to length of df.data[first_col] as List[Any]
        
        Note: Check each row for duplicates
        For i from 0 to (row_count minus 1):
            Let current_row_values be empty list
            For each col_name in df.columns:
                If df.data contains key col_name:
                    Let col_data be df.data[col_name] as List[Any]
                    If i is less than length of col_data:
                        Add col_data at index i to current_row_values
            
            Note: Check if this row already exists
            Let is_duplicate be false
            For each existing_row in unique_rows:
                If lists_are_equal with list1 as current_row_values and list2 as existing_row:
                    Set is_duplicate to true
                    Break
            
            Note: Add row if not duplicate
            If not is_duplicate:
                Add current_row_values to unique_rows
                Let col_index be 0
                For each col_name in df.columns:
                    If col_index is less than length of current_row_values:
                        Let col_list be unique_data[col_name] as List[Any]
                        Add current_row_values at index col_index to col_list
                        Set unique_data[col_name] to col_list
                    Set col_index to col_index plus 1
        
        Let deduplicated_df be df_core.DataFrame with:
            columns as df.columns
            index as create_sequential_index with count as length of unique_rows
            data as unique_data
            metadata as df.metadata
        
        Return df_core.DataFrameSuccess with data as deduplicated_df
    
    Catch error:
        Return df_core.DataFrameError with error as df_core.DataFrameErrorInfo with:
            message as "Duplicate removal failed"
            operation as "drop_duplicates"

Process called \"parse_simple_number\" that takes input as String returns Float:
    Note: Parse simple numeric strings
    Try:
        Note: Handle basic numeric parsing for common cases
        Let result be 0.0
        Let is_negative be false
        
        Note: Check for negative
        If length of input is greater than 0:
            Let first_char be substring_from_position with text as input and start_pos as 0 and length as 1
            If first_char is equal to \"-\":
                Set is_negative to true
                Let remaining_input be substring_from_position with text as input and start_pos as 1
                Set result to parse_positive_number with text as remaining_input
            Else:
                Set result to parse_positive_number with text as input
        
        If is_negative:
            Return result times (-1.0)
        Else:
            Return result
    
    Catch error:
        Return 0.0

Process called \"parse_positive_number\" that takes text as String returns Float:
    Note: Parse positive number string
    Try:
        Let result be 0.0
        Let decimal_part be 0.0
        Let decimal_divisor be 1.0
        Let has_decimal be false
        
        Note: Parse digit by digit
        Let pos be 0
        While pos is less than length of text:
            Let char be substring_from_position with text as text and start_pos as pos and length as 1
            
            If char is equal to \".\": 
                Set has_decimal to true
            Else:
                Let digit_val be simple_char_to_digit with char as char
                If digit_val is greater than or equal to 0:
                    If has_decimal:
                        Set decimal_divisor to decimal_divisor times 10.0
                        Set decimal_part to decimal_part plus (digit_val as Float) divided by decimal_divisor
                    Else:
                        Set result to result times 10.0 plus (digit_val as Float)
            
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        
        Return result plus decimal_part
    
    Catch error:
        Return 0.0

Process called \"simple_char_to_digit\" that takes char as String returns Integer:
