Process called \"lists_are_equal\" that takes list1 as List[Any] and list2 as List[Any] returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if two lists have identical contents
    Try:
        If length of list1 is not equal to length of list2:
            Return false
        
        For i from 0 to (length of list1 minus 1):
            Let val1 be list1 at index i
            Let val2 be list2 at index i
            
            Match val1:
                When Integer:
                    Match val2:
                        When Integer:
                            If (val1 as Integer) is not equal to (val2 as Integer):
                                Return false
                        Otherwise:
                            Return false
                When Float:
                    Match val2:
                        When Float:
                            Let diff be calculate_absolute_difference with a as (val1 as Float) and b as (val2 as Float)
                            If diff is greater than 0.0001:
                                Return false
                        Otherwise:
                            Return false
                When String:
                    Match val2:
                        When String:
                            If (val1 as String) is not equal to (val2 as String):
                                Return false
                        Otherwise:
                            Return false
                Otherwise:
                    Return false
        
        Return true
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called \"create_sequential_index\" that takes count as Integer returns List[Any]:
    Note: Create sequential index from 0 to count-1
    Let index_list be empty list
    For i from 0 to (count minus 1):
        Add i to index_list
    Return index_list